      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve executed the process for `process_rule_id = 'J09D'` as specified. Summary of what was done:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09D_temp` from `decision_table` for all rows where `TOUR` starts with `J09D`, adding an empty `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\n   - To `KSA` for houses (`HAUS`) with fewer than 3 distinct `EQUNR`.\n   - To `EVU` for all other houses.\n   - Overwrote to `EVU` for all rows where `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`.\n3. Joined `J09D_temp` with:\n   - `eablg` on `Installation = ANLAGE`.\n   - `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`.\n4. Applied the rule for sales vs. net data:\n   - For each `EQUNR`, if sales data exists, the exported fields come from `sales_master` (TITLE, name, address, email, etc.).\n   - Otherwise, data comes from `net_master`. This is implemented using `COALESCE(sales_master.col, net_master.col)`.\n5. Exported the final result (27,633 rows) to `J09D.csv` with exactly these columns:  \n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n6. Sent the CSV as an email attachment to `meter.readings@evu.com` for the EVU team.\n7. Dropped the temporary table `J09D_temp`.\n\nThe process for J09D is now complete.",
